It functions by emitting laser beams and measuring the time it takes for these beams to reflect off objects and return to the sensor, thus calculating the distance and location of those objects within its field of view (Lidar Model GUI - Scan Pattern (Rotating)). In real-time simulation, if the rotating lidar traces too many rays per second, it will result in the LIDAR model slowing down and its frequency decreasing.
